step1_Ensemble_sdm.R
Constructs an ensemble Species Distribution Model (SDM) to predict current and future spatial patterns of habitat suitability.

step2_RDA.R
Performs Redundancy Analysis (RDA) to identify candidate adaptive SNPs significantly associated with key climatic drivers.

step3_Lfmm.R
Executes Latent Factor Mixed Models (LFMM) to rigorously filter climate-adaptive genetic markers while controlling for population structure.

step4.gf_model_training.R
Integrates environmental and allele frequency data to train and save the baseline Gradient Forest (GF) model for predicting spatial genetic turnover.

step5.calc_genomic_offset.R
Utilizes the trained GF model to batch-calculate standard Genomic Offset (Euclidean distance) across multiple future climate scenarios.

step6.calc_forward_reverse_offset.R
Exhaustively computes Local, Forward, and Reverse (LFR) spatial genetic offsets, generating multi-band RGB rasters for ternary visualization in ArcGIS.
